WEBVTT

00:00.250 --> 00:02.017
♪

00:04.105 --> 00:06.772
whoa, what do I smell
coming from the kitchen?

00:06.857 --> 00:09.892
Could that be
the delicious aroma of...

00:10.945 --> 00:12.361
Nothing?

00:12.480 --> 00:14.646
Seriously? I thought it was
my night off from cooking.

00:14.765 --> 00:17.149
Sorry, dad, but I've got
a big report due tomorrow.

00:17.267 --> 00:18.200
And I have
nothing to do,

00:18.319 --> 00:19.651
but it's also
due tomorrow.

00:21.122 --> 00:22.204
Why don't we get take out?

00:22.323 --> 00:24.740
Okay. So what'll it be?
I'm thinking pizza.

00:24.825 --> 00:26.041
Really, dad?
I was thinking burgers.

00:26.160 --> 00:27.076
Burgers sound good.

00:27.211 --> 00:28.410
Well, why don't
we be fair

00:28.546 --> 00:30.713
and put it to
a reynolds family vote?

00:30.798 --> 00:31.997
All in favor of burgers,
say "aye".

00:32.083 --> 00:32.998
-Aye!
-Aye!

00:33.084 --> 00:34.383
Two out of three.
Burgers it is.

00:34.885 --> 00:36.719
Ugh, but I had
a burger for lunch.

00:36.804 --> 00:37.886
And you know
what they say,

00:38.005 --> 00:40.255
"two burgers a day
and your tummy will pay."

00:42.143 --> 00:43.058
sorry, dad.
That's just the way

00:43.177 --> 00:45.010
the reynolds family
vote works.

00:45.763 --> 00:46.678
(doorbell rings)

00:46.764 --> 00:48.397
all in favor of dad
getting the door.

00:48.516 --> 00:49.398
-Aye!
-Aye!

00:49.483 --> 00:51.683
I guess I will be
getting the door.

00:53.237 --> 00:54.803
A delivery
for max reynolds.

00:54.905 --> 00:55.771
Sign here please.

00:57.575 --> 00:59.608
Uh, that's just
a squiggly line.

01:00.945 --> 01:02.361
If you don't care,
I don't care.

01:02.446 --> 01:03.278
Okay.

01:03.864 --> 01:04.747
Thanks.

01:06.951 --> 01:08.117
-What's that?
-I don't know.

01:08.252 --> 01:09.585
It says it's
from some lawyer.

01:09.703 --> 01:10.753
What?

01:10.838 --> 01:12.621
I barely bumped
that other car.

01:14.208 --> 01:15.124
It's not about that.

01:15.259 --> 01:16.458
Well, then, there
was no other car.

01:18.129 --> 01:19.762
Oh no.

01:19.847 --> 01:21.964
It says our
great aunt helen
passed away.

01:23.017 --> 01:25.100
Wow. It says
here she was 104.

01:25.186 --> 01:26.501
Aw, what a shame.

01:26.604 --> 01:27.886
Who's
great aunt helen?

01:27.972 --> 01:29.638
Oh, you didn't
know her, noodle.

01:29.774 --> 01:33.058
She was this really
eccentric, whimsical woman.

01:33.177 --> 01:33.976
Ah, do you
remember when

01:34.061 --> 01:35.477
she got that
pet ostrich?

01:35.613 --> 01:37.029
How could I forget?
That's when I learned

01:37.148 --> 01:38.147
you don't keep a sandwich

01:38.232 --> 01:40.065
in your back pocket
around an ostrich.

01:40.184 --> 01:41.817
My tushy still
has nightmares.

01:42.903 --> 01:44.987
So what does the rest
of the letter say?

01:45.072 --> 01:46.155
Not much,
it's just a bunch

01:46.240 --> 01:47.206
of legal gibberish.

01:47.324 --> 01:49.324
Blah. Blah. Blah.
Oh!

01:49.410 --> 01:51.410
Oh! Mom, it says here

01:51.528 --> 01:53.295
she left us
some money
in her will.

01:53.414 --> 01:55.247
-You're kidding!
-Woo-hoo!

01:55.332 --> 01:56.248
It's our
lucky day!

01:56.366 --> 01:59.134
Oh, not for you
aunt helen.

01:59.870 --> 02:01.420
So how much
we talking here?

02:01.538 --> 02:02.504
Are you rich?

02:02.590 --> 02:03.639
Am I going to
become a spoiled brat?

02:03.757 --> 02:04.807
Please say yes.

02:06.060 --> 02:08.677
Not quite.
Let's just say, it's not enough
to change our whole lives,

02:08.762 --> 02:10.312
but it could certainly
change a month or two.

02:10.898 --> 02:11.680
Hold on.

02:12.316 --> 02:13.482
There's one condition.

02:13.601 --> 02:15.818
Oh no, I've got
to take care
of the ostrich.

02:17.571 --> 02:19.488
No. It says we have
to use the money

02:19.607 --> 02:20.656
to buy something
we wouldn't

02:20.774 --> 02:22.774
normally buy
for ourselves.

02:22.893 --> 02:23.859
Something fun.

02:23.944 --> 02:25.861
This is so awesome!

02:25.996 --> 02:28.030
We get free money
to have fun!

02:28.165 --> 02:29.665
I know!
How sweet is this?!

02:29.783 --> 02:31.283
Can life get
any better?

02:32.786 --> 02:34.119
All:
Sorry, aunt helen.

02:35.339 --> 02:37.456
(theme music playing)

02:38.876 --> 02:41.260
♪<i> like father, like daughter,</i>
<i> we don't always agree</i> ♪

02:41.378 --> 02:43.762
♪<i> but looking at you</i>
<i> is like looking at me</i> ♪

02:43.881 --> 02:48.550
♪<i> the more things change,</i>
<i> the more they stay the same</i> ♪

02:48.686 --> 02:51.053
♪<i> like father, like daughter,</i>
<i> from different times</i> ♪

02:51.138 --> 02:53.255
♪<i> taking all the best</i>
<i> from your decade and mine</i> ♪

02:53.357 --> 02:57.025
♪<i> the more things change</i> ♪

02:57.111 --> 02:58.861
♪<i> the more they stay the same</i> ♪

02:58.946 --> 03:00.863
<i> ♪ do, do, do-do, do, do ♪</i>

03:00.948 --> 03:02.197
<i> ♪ do, do ♪</i>

03:02.283 --> 03:04.700
<i>♪ the more they stay the same ♪</i>

03:06.403 --> 03:07.903
♪ ♪

03:08.289 --> 03:09.905
(singing to himself)

03:13.544 --> 03:15.410
I ess whoever said
money doesn't buy happiness

03:15.496 --> 03:16.912
hasn't seen you
this morning.

03:16.997 --> 03:18.080
You should've seen
me a minute ago.

03:18.215 --> 03:19.631
I was doing
my happy dance.

03:20.050 --> 03:22.417
Whoa, here it
comes again.

03:23.804 --> 03:25.554
So, have you decided
what you're gonna do

03:25.673 --> 03:27.222
with the money
great aunt helen
left you?

03:27.308 --> 03:28.223
I was thinking
about it all night

03:28.342 --> 03:29.925
and I have got
the perfect idea.

03:30.060 --> 03:31.927
Something the whole
family can enjoy.

03:32.012 --> 03:33.562
I was thinking
the exact same thing.

03:33.647 --> 03:34.780
And I also
have an idea.

03:35.482 --> 03:36.515
Okay.

03:36.633 --> 03:37.599
Let's hear it.

03:37.735 --> 03:39.685
(drum roll)

03:39.803 --> 03:41.770
I was thinking
a boat.

03:41.855 --> 03:42.604
A boat?!

03:42.740 --> 03:44.439
And I was thinking
hot tub.

03:44.525 --> 03:45.440
Hot tub?!

03:45.576 --> 03:48.443
Whoa, those are
both awesome ideas.

03:48.529 --> 03:49.611
Well, when you're
ready to put it to

03:49.697 --> 03:51.580
a reynolds family vote,
let me know.

03:51.665 --> 03:52.531
-Boat!
-Hot tub!

03:52.616 --> 03:54.833
Wow!
I guess you
were ready.

03:54.952 --> 03:55.784
Well, syd, looks like you

03:55.920 --> 03:56.952
are the deciding vote,

03:57.087 --> 03:58.203
so what's it gonna be?

03:58.322 --> 03:59.254
Aw syd,
is your arm sore

03:59.373 --> 04:00.289
from fencing
practice?

04:00.374 --> 04:01.423
Let me help you
with that.

04:01.926 --> 04:03.342
Just say hot tub.
Two little words.

04:03.460 --> 04:05.344
Just say boat.
It's only one
little word.

04:05.963 --> 04:07.095
How 'bout six
little words?

04:07.214 --> 04:08.764
Can I have
my arms back?

04:10.301 --> 04:12.351
You know what,
they're just both
such great ideas,

04:12.469 --> 04:13.852
I need time
to think about this.

04:13.971 --> 04:15.354
Absolutely. No pressure.

04:15.472 --> 04:17.139
A boat's a big decision.

04:17.274 --> 04:18.607
You know a great place

04:18.692 --> 04:20.508
to think about
a difficult decision?

04:20.611 --> 04:21.810
A hot tub!

04:21.895 --> 04:23.812
Uh, syd,
why don't I make you

04:23.948 --> 04:25.480
a yummy breakfast before school?

04:25.566 --> 04:26.615
Let me make
your favorite,

04:26.700 --> 04:27.682
french toast.

04:27.785 --> 04:29.201
Or I could drive you

04:29.320 --> 04:31.119
and we could get
rainbow bagels.

04:31.205 --> 04:32.154
You love those.

04:33.290 --> 04:34.957
Okay, I know what
I'm voting for.

04:35.042 --> 04:35.874
Both:
What?!

04:35.993 --> 04:37.409
Having breakfast
at school. See ya!

04:38.545 --> 04:40.162
♪ ♪

04:45.619 --> 04:46.451
hey, boys.

04:46.587 --> 04:47.386
Hi, mom.

04:47.504 --> 04:48.470
How was work?

04:48.555 --> 04:50.055
Tell me all
about your day,

04:50.157 --> 04:51.840
and don't leave
out a thing.

04:51.976 --> 04:53.175
Okay, what do you want?

04:53.894 --> 04:55.310
Ooh, straight down
to business.

04:55.429 --> 04:56.478
I like her style.

04:57.381 --> 04:59.314
There's an amazing
rap concert
tomorrow night

04:59.433 --> 05:00.515
and I wanna go.

05:00.651 --> 05:01.933
Check out this flyer.

05:04.071 --> 05:06.355
Ooh, the tickets
are awfully pricey.

05:06.490 --> 05:07.389
That's because
it's gonna be

05:07.491 --> 05:09.524
the biggest lineup
of rappers ever.

05:09.660 --> 05:11.610
Dollar-wise, it's
a pretty good deal.

05:11.695 --> 05:13.495
Lot of rhymes
for your dimes.

05:15.349 --> 05:16.315
I don't know, max.
It's on a--

05:16.417 --> 05:18.000
school night?
I know.

05:18.118 --> 05:19.951
But I'm going with
the school rap club.

05:20.037 --> 05:21.336
It's practically
homework.

05:21.455 --> 05:23.205
-But it's--
-all the way downtown?

05:23.340 --> 05:25.490
That's why our
music teacher's coming
as a chaperone.

05:25.592 --> 05:27.376
-What did--
-all the other parents say?

05:27.511 --> 05:28.627
-Yes.
-Would you let me--

05:28.712 --> 05:30.462
finish your sentences?
Of course.

05:32.516 --> 05:34.516
Ms. Reynolds, you know
I want what's best for max

05:34.601 --> 05:35.967
as much as you do.

05:36.053 --> 05:37.719
I think you should
let him come with us.

05:37.855 --> 05:39.354
I'm sorry, leo.
I always forget.

05:39.440 --> 05:41.690
Did I give birth to max
or did you?

05:42.559 --> 05:44.059
I'm trying not to
picture either.

05:45.896 --> 05:47.229
Please, mom.

05:47.364 --> 05:49.314
I really want to go
to this concert.

05:51.235 --> 05:52.901
I'm gonna have
to say no.

05:53.954 --> 05:54.870
What?

05:55.873 --> 05:57.539
I don't understand.

05:57.875 --> 06:00.876
I'm sorry, max,
but that's my answer.

06:03.330 --> 06:04.629
Did you hear that?

06:04.748 --> 06:06.882
I explained
everything to her.

06:06.967 --> 06:07.999
I don't get it.

06:08.085 --> 06:09.084
Sorry, buddy.

06:09.219 --> 06:10.385
If it makes you
feel any better,

06:10.504 --> 06:11.837
I'll only have
half the fun.

06:11.922 --> 06:14.172
I thought you were gonna
say you weren't going.

06:14.258 --> 06:15.424
Oh, that's
not happening.

06:16.260 --> 06:17.259
♪ ♪

06:18.929 --> 06:19.794
I got your text.

06:19.897 --> 06:21.179
I can't believe
you have a choice

06:21.265 --> 06:23.631
between a boat
and a hot tub.

06:23.734 --> 06:24.766
All my choices
are between

06:24.852 --> 06:26.852
which brother to sit
next to at dinner:

06:26.937 --> 06:29.237
Eats-all-my-food
or eats-with-his-hands.

06:30.574 --> 06:31.690
And honestly,
I'd be fine

06:31.775 --> 06:33.641
with either a boat
or hot tub.

06:33.744 --> 06:35.110
But whichever
one I choose,

06:35.245 --> 06:37.496
my dad or my grandma
is gonna be really
disappointed.

06:37.614 --> 06:38.914
Syd, they'll be fine.

06:38.999 --> 06:39.865
They're adults.

06:39.950 --> 06:41.700
They're used to
disappointment.

06:43.203 --> 06:45.170
The only thing
you should be
asking yourself is,

06:45.255 --> 06:46.171
"what do you want?"

06:46.373 --> 06:47.706
you're right.
It's my vote.

06:47.791 --> 06:49.674
And I think you should
use it on a hot tub.

06:49.760 --> 06:50.792
No! Boat!

06:50.928 --> 06:52.260
No! Hot tub!

06:52.346 --> 06:53.628
Okay,
I'm gonna stop.
No, I won't!

06:53.764 --> 06:54.629
-Yes you will.
-Thank you.

06:55.048 --> 06:56.047
(phone ping)

06:57.634 --> 06:59.667
oh, it's my dad.
He wants to see me
in the backyard.

06:59.770 --> 07:01.803
Okay. I've got to get
back home for dinner.

07:01.889 --> 07:04.639
Tonight I get to sit
next to chews-too-loud.

07:04.775 --> 07:05.941
That's my dad.

07:07.111 --> 07:08.276
You know what?
Why am I making

07:08.362 --> 07:10.278
such a big deal
out of this?

07:10.397 --> 07:11.530
I'm sure my
grandma and dad

07:11.615 --> 07:13.148
will accept whichever
one I choose.

07:17.788 --> 07:19.321
Ahoy there, matey!

07:21.325 --> 07:22.407
Dad?

07:22.493 --> 07:23.691
No.

07:23.794 --> 07:24.910
Call me...

07:24.995 --> 07:26.161
Captain dad.

07:26.713 --> 07:27.746
♪ ♪

07:30.134 --> 07:31.049
♪ ♪

07:32.603 --> 07:34.536
you bought the boat?

07:34.671 --> 07:36.521
But I didn't
even vote yet.

07:36.607 --> 07:38.240
I didn't buy the boat.
I convinced the salesman

07:38.342 --> 07:40.192
to let me take it
home for an hour.

07:40.277 --> 07:41.943
I thought you should
experience what it's like

07:42.029 --> 07:44.146
being on
the<i> s.S. Sydney.</i>

07:44.882 --> 07:45.780
Wow.

07:45.866 --> 07:47.282
You're naming it
after me?

07:47.367 --> 07:49.367
You've never named
anything after me.

07:49.453 --> 07:50.535
Well, except me.

07:50.621 --> 07:51.987
Well, I named it
after you

07:52.072 --> 07:54.489
because no one
will enjoy it
more than you will.

07:54.992 --> 07:55.874
No one.

07:57.244 --> 07:58.326
Dad,

07:58.412 --> 07:59.628
come on,

07:59.746 --> 08:01.796
you're just trying
to influence my vote.

08:01.899 --> 08:02.697
Max: What?!

08:02.833 --> 08:04.199
If I was trying
to influence you,

08:04.301 --> 08:06.201
I would say
imagine yourself

08:06.336 --> 08:09.588
on a gorgeous lake
water skiing.

08:09.723 --> 08:11.256
But that's not the
kind of guy I am.

08:13.010 --> 08:14.593
I can go water skiing?

08:14.678 --> 08:15.677
Oh, yeah.

08:15.762 --> 08:17.179
Now sit back and relax
while I take you

08:17.297 --> 08:18.847
on a little tour
of the lake.

08:23.854 --> 08:25.604
What a perfect day.

08:26.240 --> 08:27.138
Oh, look!

08:27.357 --> 08:28.573
There's the old boat house
where they sell

08:28.659 --> 08:31.243
the best ice cream
in the pacific northwest.

08:31.328 --> 08:33.078
You and olive
are gonna love it.

08:33.163 --> 08:34.162
Olive's with me?

08:34.248 --> 08:35.080
Oh, yeah.

08:35.199 --> 08:36.665
She's sitting right
in front of you.

08:36.783 --> 08:38.166
Wearing two life jackets

08:38.285 --> 08:40.085
and holding
an emergency beacon.

08:41.922 --> 08:43.672
Hold on.
Here comes a boat.

08:43.790 --> 08:45.340
Oh, and look
who's on board.

08:45.459 --> 08:46.925
Cute teenage boys?

08:47.010 --> 08:49.010
Well, I was gonna
say old charlie, the guy
who runs the boat house.

08:49.129 --> 08:50.879
But let's go with yours.

08:51.715 --> 08:53.798
Hi guys!

08:55.802 --> 08:58.353
Gotta say I'm kinda
liking the boating life.

08:58.472 --> 09:01.439
But I still have to
consider grandma's hot tub.

09:01.558 --> 09:04.392
Of course.
A hot tub is a nice choice,

09:04.478 --> 09:05.777
but you're in and out
in 20 minutes.

09:05.862 --> 09:06.778
And I don't know about you,

09:06.897 --> 09:09.364
but I get all pruney
in the hot water.

09:09.483 --> 09:11.116
Yeah, nobody wants
to see that.

09:12.903 --> 09:14.819
But, hey, it's your decision.

09:15.656 --> 09:16.788
And while you're
thinking about it,

09:16.873 --> 09:19.691
why don't you drive
the boat back to the dock?

09:19.793 --> 09:20.992
Seriously?

09:21.128 --> 09:22.627
I get to drive the boat?

09:23.714 --> 09:24.796
Aye, aye, captain.

09:30.637 --> 09:31.720
That's it.

09:31.838 --> 09:33.805
That's it.
You got it.

09:33.890 --> 09:35.090
Wait a minute.
Are you steering back

09:35.175 --> 09:36.641
toward that boat
full of boys?

09:36.727 --> 09:38.476
Don't question your captain.

09:38.562 --> 09:39.811
(honks)

09:39.896 --> 09:42.847
ahoy boys!

09:45.485 --> 09:48.019
(scoffs)
how low can he go?

09:48.155 --> 09:50.071
Who taught him to play so dirty?

09:50.157 --> 09:51.606
Oh right, it was me.

09:52.359 --> 09:53.942
♪ ♪

09:55.996 --> 09:57.078
I still can't believe

09:57.164 --> 09:58.613
she said no to
the rap concert.

09:58.699 --> 10:00.398
I'm at a loss for words.

10:00.500 --> 10:01.416
No, I'm not.

10:01.501 --> 10:03.451
Dang, dang, and double dang!

10:05.339 --> 10:07.038
Sorry, max, but it
needed to be said.

10:09.176 --> 10:11.626
Might as well just add
this "no" to my collection.

10:11.712 --> 10:12.544
What collection?

10:16.433 --> 10:17.432
Max:<i> Please, mom.</i>

10:17.551 --> 10:19.301
<i> I really want to go</i>
<i> to this concert.</i>

10:19.386 --> 10:20.685
Judy:<i> I'm gonna have to say no.</i>

10:21.021 --> 10:22.354
You actually
recorded her?

10:22.439 --> 10:24.606
I've been recording
her say "no" forever.

10:25.475 --> 10:28.193
Max:<i> Mom, can I go on that new</i>
<i> roller coaster at seven flags?</i>

10:28.312 --> 10:29.694
Judy:<i> No. I'm sorry, max.</i>

10:29.813 --> 10:30.979
(tape spooling)

10:31.064 --> 10:32.280
max:<i> Can I go to</i>
<i> skateboarding camp?</i>

10:32.366 --> 10:34.199
Judy:<i> I already told you no.</i>

10:34.701 --> 10:35.734
And here's
a small sampling

10:35.869 --> 10:36.951
of her
greatest hits.

10:37.454 --> 10:39.738
Judy:<i> You heard me. No!</i>
<i> And that's final.</i>

10:39.873 --> 10:41.456
<i> No. No!</i>

10:41.575 --> 10:42.957
<i> Yes. Wait!</i>

10:43.076 --> 10:44.075
<i> I mean no.</i>

10:45.829 --> 10:47.329
Wow, that's
so shocking.

10:47.414 --> 10:48.413
You think
your mom realizes

10:48.548 --> 10:49.748
how often
she says no?

10:50.550 --> 10:51.499
Maybe not.

10:52.336 --> 10:53.218
Ya know,

10:53.804 --> 10:55.136
I bet if I played
this tape for her,

10:55.222 --> 10:56.471
she'd finally
hear herself

10:56.590 --> 10:57.889
and say yes
to the concert.

10:57.974 --> 10:59.507
You think your mom's
just gonna sit there

10:59.593 --> 11:01.810
listening to herself
say no a hundred times?

11:01.928 --> 11:02.927
That's true.

11:04.147 --> 11:05.930
I should probably
dress it up a little.

11:06.850 --> 11:07.965
I have an idea, leo.

11:08.068 --> 11:09.100
Ya know,
coming from you,

11:09.236 --> 11:10.352
those are
the scariest words

11:10.437 --> 11:11.436
in the english
language.

11:13.940 --> 11:15.990
Olive, my dad made
some really good points,

11:16.109 --> 11:18.276
so I think I'm gonna vote boat.

11:20.280 --> 11:22.163
Hold on.
Grandma wants to see me.

11:22.282 --> 11:23.415
Call you later.

11:29.256 --> 11:30.755
Come on in, the water's fine!

11:32.542 --> 11:33.425
Oh, boy.

11:33.543 --> 11:34.776
♪ ♪

11:37.297 --> 11:39.013
mom, can I see you
for a minute?

11:39.132 --> 11:41.132
Sure, what is it, max?

11:41.218 --> 11:43.134
I've been thinking
about yesterday.

11:43.720 --> 11:45.270
Words were exchanged.

11:45.355 --> 11:46.938
Tempers flared.

11:47.023 --> 11:48.473
It doesn't matter
who was right.

11:49.276 --> 11:50.191
It was me,

11:50.310 --> 11:51.476
but it doesn't matter.

11:52.479 --> 11:54.813
Well, almost thank you
for that almost apology.

11:56.950 --> 11:58.066
My point is,

11:58.151 --> 11:59.401
I was wondering,

11:59.486 --> 12:01.619
do you know how often
you say "no" to me?

12:01.705 --> 12:04.656
At the risk of adding
another one... No.

12:05.409 --> 12:07.242
Well, maybe this
will remind you.

12:07.327 --> 12:09.577
Okay, people.
It's time
to get real

12:09.663 --> 12:12.530
with some rhymes from
grand master max!

12:12.632 --> 12:13.915
Hit it!

12:14.418 --> 12:16.801
(rap beat playing)

12:16.887 --> 12:18.253
♪ let me tell you
'bout a concert ♪

12:18.338 --> 12:19.554
♪ I really wanna go ♪

12:19.639 --> 12:20.972
♪ everybody gonna be there ♪

12:21.057 --> 12:22.474
- ♪ but my momma said... ♪
-judy:<i> No!</i>

12:22.592 --> 12:23.808
Leo: ♪ you really
can't go? ♪

12:23.894 --> 12:25.393
♪ that's right,
she said no ♪

12:25.512 --> 12:26.561
♪ can I go swimming ♪

12:26.680 --> 12:27.879
♪ or borrow some dough ♪

12:27.981 --> 12:29.514
♪ the woman always
answers with ♪

12:29.649 --> 12:30.682
judy:
<i> No, no, no!</i>

12:30.817 --> 12:32.150
♪ and just
when I think ♪

12:32.235 --> 12:33.435
♪ that's all the
no she's got ♪

12:33.520 --> 12:35.219
♪ that's when she
hits me with an ♪

12:35.322 --> 12:36.354
judy:
<i> Absolutely not!</i>

12:36.490 --> 12:37.856
♪ so once before
I'm grown up ♪

12:37.991 --> 12:39.056
♪ and leave the nest ♪

12:39.159 --> 12:42.026
♪ can I ask for
the concert
to be a yes ♪

12:42.112 --> 12:44.779
♪ everybody's going
and there's a chaperone ♪

12:44.865 --> 12:47.282
♪ seems to me the lady
could throw the kid a bone ♪

12:47.400 --> 12:48.950
max:
♪ so let me ask
again, mom ♪

12:49.068 --> 12:50.368
♪ will you let me go ♪

12:50.504 --> 12:53.204
-♪ if you're being fair,
you can't say... ♪
-judy:<i> No!</i>

12:54.207 --> 12:55.340
♪ ♪

12:59.963 --> 13:03.465
wow, I didn't realize
I've said no to you
that many times.

13:04.050 --> 13:06.050
So, I can go
to the concert?

13:06.386 --> 13:07.469
I'm sorry, max,

13:08.188 --> 13:09.721
but I'm still gonna
have to say no.

13:14.227 --> 13:16.194
It's like she
wasn't even listening.

13:16.596 --> 13:17.812
You know what,

13:17.931 --> 13:19.898
I don't think she
wants me to be happy.

13:20.317 --> 13:21.316
But let's ask her.

13:22.619 --> 13:26.371
Judy:<i> No, no, no, no,</i>
<i> no, no, no, no, no, no.</i>

13:26.823 --> 13:28.156
If we ever do get
her to say yes,

13:28.241 --> 13:30.325
I bet we can do
a really sweet remix.

13:33.713 --> 13:34.662
Okay, not the time.

13:35.332 --> 13:38.666
♪ ♪

13:40.620 --> 13:42.754
grandma,
I have to admit,

13:42.839 --> 13:44.839
this hot tub
is awesome.

13:44.958 --> 13:47.759
And b-t-dubs,
love the robe.

13:48.929 --> 13:50.929
Wait, you didn't buy
this hot tub, right?

13:51.965 --> 13:53.932
Just wink and it's yours.

13:56.736 --> 13:59.821
Now picture yourself in
your very own hot tub.

13:59.906 --> 14:03.307
Water bubbling all around,
not a care in the world.

14:03.577 --> 14:05.743
(sighs)
say it with me.

14:06.279 --> 14:07.445
(sighs together)

14:08.782 --> 14:11.482
feel the water jets
working their magic.

14:11.585 --> 14:12.834
Oh, yeah.

14:12.953 --> 14:15.620
That's hitting
the backpack muscles
real nice.

14:17.657 --> 14:19.541
Grandma,
I love this, but

14:19.626 --> 14:20.592
it kind of feels like

14:20.677 --> 14:22.343
you're trying to
influence my vote.

14:22.546 --> 14:23.711
What?!

14:23.797 --> 14:25.096
If I were trying
to influence you,

14:25.181 --> 14:26.347
I'd tell you
that this thing

14:26.433 --> 14:28.600
has twenty-six
adjustable jets,

14:28.718 --> 14:29.968
built-in speakers,

14:30.103 --> 14:33.337
and led lights
that change color
with the music.

14:33.440 --> 14:34.472
But I don't play that game.

14:36.443 --> 14:39.644
Wow. This hot tub
can do anything.

14:39.779 --> 14:40.945
Can it do my homework?

14:41.031 --> 14:43.948
No, but it can make you
forget you have any.

14:45.201 --> 14:48.319
Look, I'm the first to admit
that a boat would be cool,

14:48.455 --> 14:51.406
but this is portland,
where it's cold half the year.

14:51.491 --> 14:52.356
That's true.

14:52.876 --> 14:54.409
But it would still
be a lot of fun.

14:54.995 --> 14:57.128
Tubing, water skiing.

14:57.213 --> 14:59.297
Waving at boats
full of cute boys.

14:59.966 --> 15:01.749
That's who's at my lake.

15:02.719 --> 15:03.668
Sounds great.

15:03.803 --> 15:06.137
But the closest lake
is an hour away.

15:06.222 --> 15:07.422
With a hot tub,

15:07.540 --> 15:10.091
you and olive can pop
right in here after school.

15:10.209 --> 15:10.975
Olive's here?

15:11.094 --> 15:12.176
Yeah!

15:12.262 --> 15:15.212
She's right there with
floaties and a nose plug.

15:15.315 --> 15:16.848
(chuckles)

15:16.933 --> 15:18.650
we would have fun.

15:18.768 --> 15:23.521
In fact, why not invite
all the amigas over for
a hot tub dance party?

15:23.607 --> 15:25.440
Hey, emmy, crank up the jams!

15:25.558 --> 15:27.325
Whoa, sophia,

15:27.410 --> 15:30.111
I didn't know you could
do the worm in the hot tub.

15:30.697 --> 15:32.830
Both:
Go sophia! Go sophia!

15:36.903 --> 15:38.119
What's going on here?

15:39.122 --> 15:40.738
I can't believe you
would go behind my back

15:40.840 --> 15:42.507
to try and sway
syd's vote

15:42.592 --> 15:44.909
by putting a hot tub
in our backyard.

15:45.011 --> 15:48.296
Says the man who put
a boat in our backyard.

15:48.381 --> 15:50.298
Ahoy matey!

15:50.383 --> 15:51.966
Well, that's totally different.

15:53.136 --> 15:54.636
Because...

15:54.721 --> 15:56.387
Well, that's totally different.

15:58.091 --> 15:59.223
Give it up, max.

15:59.309 --> 16:00.308
You're not getting the boat.

16:00.426 --> 16:01.392
You know what,

16:01.478 --> 16:02.977
this is exactly like
when I was a kid.

16:03.096 --> 16:04.612
All you did was
say no to me.

16:04.731 --> 16:06.531
Well, this time,
I'm saying no to you.

16:06.616 --> 16:08.232
We are getting that boat.

16:08.785 --> 16:10.401
(shouts)
you mean hot tub.

16:10.770 --> 16:11.736
(door slams)

16:12.939 --> 16:13.771
is it gettin' hot
in this tub

16:13.873 --> 16:14.906
or is it just me?

16:15.458 --> 16:16.574
♪ ♪

16:18.044 --> 16:19.027
♪ ♪

16:19.980 --> 16:21.179
well, great aunt helen's gift

16:21.281 --> 16:23.231
has officially become
a nightmare.

16:23.316 --> 16:26.284
I've never seen my dad and
grandma so angry at each other.

16:26.369 --> 16:28.936
But they both pictured me in
the boat and the hot tub, right?

16:29.039 --> 16:30.038
-Olive!
-Just checking.

16:31.558 --> 16:32.991
They aren't even
talking to each other.

16:33.743 --> 16:36.327
I'm sorry, but this
whole thing sounds silly.

16:36.413 --> 16:38.046
It's a win-win situation.

16:38.131 --> 16:40.164
I mean, let's say
your dad doesn't
get his boat.

16:40.283 --> 16:41.416
So he's all,

16:41.501 --> 16:44.252
"I have to hang out
in a hot tub. Boo-hoo."

16:45.055 --> 16:47.555
I know. They're both
being so immature.

16:47.674 --> 16:49.941
I mean, I really wanted
a new amp for christmas.

16:50.043 --> 16:51.843
Did I throw a tantrum
when I didn't get it?

16:51.911 --> 16:54.062
-A little.
-I'm a kid, that's what we do.

16:55.682 --> 16:57.465
Adults are supposed
to be better than that.

16:57.550 --> 16:58.716
What if they aren't?

16:58.852 --> 16:59.817
What if they're just

16:59.919 --> 17:02.153
bigger, louder
versions of us?

17:02.272 --> 17:03.938
That would explain a lot.

17:05.141 --> 17:06.657
(sighs)
it's awful.

17:06.776 --> 17:08.576
This was supposed
to bring the family together,

17:08.661 --> 17:10.244
but it's
tearing us apart.

17:10.330 --> 17:11.362
And I'm stuck
in the middle

17:11.448 --> 17:12.480
trying to figure
out how to give

17:12.582 --> 17:14.115
everyone what
they want.

17:14.200 --> 17:15.033
In my house,

17:15.151 --> 17:16.417
nobody gets
what they want.

17:16.536 --> 17:17.318
We cry

17:17.420 --> 17:18.486
and kick

17:18.588 --> 17:19.871
and scream.

17:19.956 --> 17:21.956
I'm beginning to think
it might be
a better system.

17:22.509 --> 17:24.092
♪ ♪

17:27.097 --> 17:28.379
hey max.
How're you doing?

17:28.465 --> 17:29.714
Mom,

17:29.799 --> 17:31.165
I'd kinda like to be alone.

17:31.267 --> 17:33.267
I hate to see you so upset.

17:34.938 --> 17:36.471
I just don't get it.

17:37.390 --> 17:39.006
Why do you say no
to me all the time?

17:39.109 --> 17:41.809
I guess I do say it
a little more
than I realized,

17:41.895 --> 17:44.645
but "all the time" is
a bit of an exaggeration.

17:46.816 --> 17:48.149
Okay, you win.

17:50.520 --> 17:52.870
All I can tell you is
I have my reasons.

17:52.989 --> 17:53.988
Can you believe that?

17:54.491 --> 17:55.323
Not really.

17:56.292 --> 17:58.126
But, I'll say yes.

17:58.878 --> 18:01.195
Somebody's gotta say it
around here for once.

18:01.297 --> 18:03.915
Look, I know it's not
as good as the concert,

18:04.033 --> 18:06.717
but how 'bout if I make
you a special night here.

18:06.836 --> 18:08.970
I'll order you
a double pepperoni pizza,

18:09.055 --> 18:10.388
you can stay up late,

18:10.507 --> 18:12.006
and watch any
movie you want.

18:12.509 --> 18:13.641
No, thanks.

18:14.644 --> 18:15.810
It doesn't make up
for missing out

18:15.895 --> 18:17.678
on the concert
with my friends.

18:18.348 --> 18:19.564
I'm sorry, max.

18:19.682 --> 18:21.149
I just hope someday
when you're older,

18:21.267 --> 18:22.683
you'll understand.

18:23.019 --> 18:24.102
♪ ♪

18:29.359 --> 18:30.641
so, syd texted you, too?

18:30.777 --> 18:33.194
If I were talking to you,
I'd say yes.

18:36.583 --> 18:38.749
I asked you guys
down here because,

18:38.835 --> 18:40.251
I made my decision.

18:40.370 --> 18:42.903
I want you to know,
that I've weighed
all the factors involved

18:43.006 --> 18:44.505
and my vote

18:44.591 --> 18:45.840
is...

18:45.959 --> 18:47.175
-Yeah?
-And?

18:47.260 --> 18:48.326
I'm not voting.

18:48.428 --> 18:50.511
Ha! In your face!

18:51.548 --> 18:54.215
Wait. Did you say
not voting or not boating?

18:55.418 --> 18:56.300
Not voting.

18:57.303 --> 18:58.853
Look at you two.

18:58.972 --> 19:01.222
This gift was
supposed to be fun,

19:01.357 --> 19:03.558
but it's making
all of us miserable.

19:03.643 --> 19:06.110
I don't even understand
why it's so important to you.

19:06.229 --> 19:08.563
Because I never got
to have fun stuff
when I was a kid.

19:08.698 --> 19:11.699
No matter what I asked for,
your grandma loved to say no.

19:11.818 --> 19:13.034
Loved it?

19:13.153 --> 19:14.819
I had to say no.

19:14.904 --> 19:17.205
I was a single mother
and money was tight.

19:17.323 --> 19:18.573
Oh, come on, I know we
weren't millionaires,

19:18.708 --> 19:20.041
but we weren't
that hard up.

19:20.126 --> 19:21.909
I never shared it with you, max,
but there were a couple of times

19:22.045 --> 19:23.878
when we almost lost the house.

19:24.164 --> 19:25.046
What?

19:25.748 --> 19:26.631
Why didn't you tell me?

19:26.749 --> 19:28.249
Because I didn't
want you to worry.

19:28.384 --> 19:30.585
No kid should have to
worry about stuff like that.

19:32.422 --> 19:33.421
I never knew.

19:33.556 --> 19:34.922
You weren't supposed to.

19:35.058 --> 19:37.058
And the only person I said
"no" to more than you,

19:37.177 --> 19:38.593
was me.

19:39.929 --> 19:42.597
Is that why you wanted
the hot tub so badly, grandma?

19:42.732 --> 19:44.432
Yes.

19:44.517 --> 19:47.068
It's just the kind of luxury
that I was never able to afford

19:47.153 --> 19:48.603
when I was raising your dad.

19:51.524 --> 19:53.107
I say it's time
for another vote.

19:53.193 --> 19:54.075
Not again.

19:54.160 --> 19:55.443
I vote hot tub.

19:56.162 --> 19:57.028
You're kidding.

19:57.664 --> 19:58.946
Wow, grandma.

19:59.082 --> 20:00.615
Looks like you're
getting a hot tub.

20:00.700 --> 20:01.782
Don't listen to him.

20:01.918 --> 20:02.750
I vote boat.

20:02.835 --> 20:03.701
What? Say what?

20:05.872 --> 20:08.873
I'm finally able to say yes,
and I'm saying yes to the boat.

20:08.991 --> 20:10.508
But mom, you did
nothing but sacrifice.

20:10.627 --> 20:11.926
You deserve a hot tub.

20:12.011 --> 20:13.327
Don't listen to him.
He's getting his boat.

20:13.429 --> 20:15.346
Ignore her.
She needs her hot tub.

20:15.465 --> 20:16.631
Sydney: Guys!

20:16.716 --> 20:18.799
Look, this isn't
getting us anywhere.

20:20.053 --> 20:22.970
Maybe we should think of another
way of resolving our problems.

20:24.107 --> 20:25.806
What if every vote
had to be unanimous?

20:25.892 --> 20:28.059
It might take longer
to work things out,

20:28.177 --> 20:30.311
but then nobody loses.

20:31.197 --> 20:32.113
I'm on board.

20:32.198 --> 20:33.481
Sounds good to me, noodle.

20:34.284 --> 20:35.683
In fact, I have
the perfect thing

20:35.785 --> 20:37.151
to test our
new system.

20:37.237 --> 20:39.070
How many think syd is
the best daughter ever?

20:40.123 --> 20:41.155
I'll vote for that.

20:41.658 --> 20:42.707
Okay, okay.

20:42.825 --> 20:44.408
In the interest
of making it unanimous,

20:44.527 --> 20:45.993
I am the best daughter.

20:48.047 --> 20:49.013
♪ ♪

20:53.035 --> 20:54.585
hey, syd,
you wanted
to see us?

20:54.671 --> 20:57.004
Yep. I think I've come up
with the perfect use

20:57.090 --> 20:58.472
for great aunt helen's gift.

20:58.558 --> 20:59.674
Really?
What is it?

21:00.226 --> 21:02.260
Well, I know how much you had
your heart set on a boat,

21:02.345 --> 21:04.478
and I know how much
you wanted a hot tub,

21:04.564 --> 21:06.063
so...

21:06.599 --> 21:09.550
We're going
on a cruise!

21:09.652 --> 21:11.102
It's a boat with
a hot tub.

21:11.220 --> 21:13.854
Wow, now that's a boat.

21:13.940 --> 21:15.773
Okay, easy. I borrowed it
from a travel agent.

21:17.944 --> 21:19.827
So, what do you say?

21:19.912 --> 21:22.029
-I'm in!
-So am I!

21:22.699 --> 21:25.416
Hey, is that
a tiny water slide?

21:25.535 --> 21:26.834
And a tiny
movie theater?

21:27.537 --> 21:29.537
And is that
a tiny karaoke bar?

21:29.622 --> 21:32.873
I cannot wait to serenade
my two favorite ladies.

21:34.177 --> 21:36.761
Okay, new vote.
No embarrassing your
daughter on the cruise.

21:36.879 --> 21:37.928
Or your mother.

21:38.047 --> 21:38.929
It's probably a good call.

21:39.015 --> 21:40.548
Hey, this new system
really works.
